channel.title: CVE Feed for iagona -- ScrutisWeb
channel.description: The latest CVEs for iagona -- ScrutisWeb

item.title: CVE-2023-38257|2023-07-18T17:17:29.939Z -- iagona -- scrutisweb
item.description: Iagona ScrutisWeb versions 2.1.37 and prior are vulnerable to an insecure direct object reference vulnerability that could allow an unauthenticated user to view profile information, including user login names and encrypted passwords.

item.title: CVE-2023-33871|2023-07-18T17:21:16.587Z -- iagona -- scrutisweb
item.description: Iagona ScrutisWeb versions 2.1.37 and prior are vulnerable to a directory traversal vulnerability that could allow an unauthenticated user to directly access any file outside the webroot.

item.title: CVE-2023-35763|2023-07-18T17:23:43.966Z -- iagona -- scrutisweb
item.description: Iagona ScrutisWeb versions 2.1.37 and prior are vulnerable to a cryptographic vulnerability that could allow an unauthenticated user to decrypt encrypted passwords into plaintext.

item.title: CVE-2023-35189|2023-07-18T17:14:57.706Z -- iagona -- scrutisweb
item.description: Iagona ScrutisWeb versions 2.1.37 and prior are vulnerable to a remote code execution vulnerability that could allow an unauthenticated user to upload a malicious payload and execute it.
